{"submission_id":"sub_17853cfb1022cba6","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T15:56:35.519Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:17853cfb1022cba61fee778942d4607b5cf26a19975362aab4aa2f5e1333779f","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_farebox_reason","label":"Farebox Revenue Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"NYCT was unfavorable by ($16.1M) mainly due to lower Subway and Bus ridership. MTA Bus was unfavorable by ($3.3M) due to lower ridership and average fare per trip, and the LIRR was unfavorable by ($1.0M) due to lower average fare per trip. These results were partially offset by a favorable variance of $2.7M at MNR mainly due to higher ridership.","subject":"Farebox Revenue","change_type":"unfavorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"unfavorable","normalized_value":"unfavorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p003_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:cbcf10b9e99bc4c8d8798026ce3fbad842d9afb83e8600a390d888a49c6a9a68","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_effc6314e4b36751","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T15:57:03.490Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:effc6314e4b36751e60be31af46ea6ffb472151ee7b1997276226dc915b4cc6b","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_toll_revenue_reason","label":"Toll Revenue Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"Toll revenue was favorable due to higher traffic volume and average toll per crossing.","subject":"Vehicle Toll Revenue","change_type":"favorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"favorable","normalized_value":"favorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p003_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:cbcf10b9e99bc4c8d8798026ce3fbad842d9afb83e8600a390d888a49c6a9a68","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_7b8dc43dfbdae37f","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T15:57:26.919Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:7b8dc43dfbdae37ff35adea3d66c456081aa2db479197db7240661276542b6b2","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_payroll_reason","label":"Payroll Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"NYCT, MTA Bus, and B&T were favorable by $25.1M, $1.1M, and $0.7M, respectively, mainly due to vacancies. The LIRR was favorable by $3.3M mainly due to both timing and lower average pay rates reflecting new hires. These results were partially offset by an unfavorable variance of ($6.5M) at MTA HQ mainly due to higher MTA PD salaries.","subject":"Payroll","change_type":"favorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"favorable","normalized_value":"favorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p003_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:cbcf10b9e99bc4c8d8798026ce3fbad842d9afb83e8600a390d888a49c6a9a68","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_6fa7f9205db2be90","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T15:57:49.722Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:6fa7f9205db2be905046d354b3939b0ee80294083929c99d14700f1896d5a56d","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_overtime_reason","label":"Overtime Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"Unfavorable results from overruns totaling ($19.8M) at NYCT and ($3.4M) at MNR were mainly due to higher vacancy/absence coverage. The LIRR was unfavorable by ($4.1M) mainly due to higher weather-related requirements, vacancy/absence coverage, scheduled service, and programmatic/routine maintenance.","subject":"Overtime","change_type":"unfavorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"unfavorable","normalized_value":"unfavorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p003_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":3,"block_id":"p003_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:cbcf10b9e99bc4c8d8798026ce3fbad842d9afb83e8600a390d888a49c6a9a68","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_352354cca4a70d72","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:04:21.497Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:352354cca4a70d7202f04d0ef4ba21abb9d97368323336293c36167c472bacee","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_subsidies_reason","label":"Subsidies Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"The favorable variance mainly reflected favorable PBT of $12.1M and City Subsidy to MTA Bus of $8.5M, both due to timing. Favorable results also reflect investment income, $6.0M due to higher interest rates, Local Operating Assistance 18-B, $4.9M, due to timing, and Urban Tax, $3.7M due to higher-than expected commercial real estate transactions in NYC. These were primarily offset by unfavorable MRT of $11.1M due to lower-than-expected mortgage activity.","subject":"Subsidies","change_type":"favorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"favorable","normalized_value":"favorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p006_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":6,"block_id":"p006_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:a94f2dd8082502ec0882f5ddaf8320535f55adb33954c7d45a4830f561f5ad03","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_f0b50ed9b6c5dadf","run_id":"2026-06-20T14-52-26-585Z_1885472-65abb0be_ingest_meeting-doc-133396","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T16:04:48.220Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:f0b50ed9b6c5dadfb6d96fca1d8f879d7e440b63164d29856aca75380783167c","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_meeting_doc_133396_professional_services_reason","label":"Professional Services Contracts Variance Reason January 2024","payload":{"claim_text":"The overall favorable outcome was mainly attributable to the timing of various expenses at the following agencies: $32.7M at MTA HQ reflecting recoveries, professional contract payments, MTA IT-related items including software services, maintenance and repairs and consulting services; $1.2M at MTA Bus due to the timing of interagency billing and lower bus technology expenses; $0.9M at B&T due to lower bond issuance fees, professional services contracts payments, and planning studies; and $0.9M at MNR reflecting lower consulting and engineering services.","subject":"Professional Service Contracts","change_type":"favorable","change_type_normalized":{"raw_text":"favorable","normalized_value":"favorable"}},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_133396","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_133396#p004_c0002","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_133396/blocks.jsonl","page_number":4,"block_id":"p004_c0002","text_sha256":"sha256:37312233f9bf5952916a58e9209ee1618782a7823399455125b6b7d55e994ff6","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
